org.jeo.vector

Class Schema

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jeo.vector.Schema
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Field>

    public class Schema
extends Object
implements Iterable<Field>
    Describes the structure of a Feature object.

    A schema is am immutable collection of named Field objects, any of which may be a geometry field.

    Author:
    Justin Deoliveira, OpenGeo

        public Field geometry()
        Derived geometry field of the schema.

        This method returns the first field that returns true from Field.isGeometry(). If no such field is found null is returned.

      • crs

        public org.osgeo.proj4j.CoordinateReferenceSystem crs()
        Derived coordinate reference system for the schema.

        If the schemas crs field is set it is retunred, other this method delegates to geometry().crs().

        Returns:
        The coordinate reference system object, or null if not available or no geometry field exists.
